snippet: The Commerce Department said that groundbreaking increased 6.5 percent to a seasonally adjusted annual pace of 1.21 million units.
abstract: Commerce Dept reports housing starts in September rose to seasonally adjusted annual rate of 1.21 million homes, rise of 6.5 percent; most of rise is attributable to 17 percent surge in multifamily housing.
lead_paragraph: The Commerce Department said that groundbreaking increased 6.5 percent to a seasonally adjusted annual pace of 1.21 million units.

headline.print_headline: Data Shows Resilience in Housing in the U.S.
headline.main: U.S. Housing Starts Increased in September
